20and%20like%20most%20parents%2C%20I've%20had%20to%20learn%20that%20not%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparenting-teens-is-a-balance-too-close-or-too-far-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eevery%20battle%20is%20worth%20fighting%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Parenting%20often%20comes%20with%20a%20long%20list%20of%20things%20we're%20supposed%20to%20correct%3A%20language%2C%20behavior%2C%20tone%2C%20attitude.%20For%20a%20long%20time%2C%20I%20reacted%20the%20way%20many%20parents%20do%20when%20I%20heard%20a%20curse%20word.%20I%20corrected%20it%20immediately%20and%20reminded%20my%20kids%20that%20those%20words%20weren't%20allowed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225712%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22family%20posing%20for%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69cbe83572abfab4a4e4f755%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author's%20kids%20started%20opening%20up%20to%20her%20more.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20I%20started%20noticing%20something.%20Most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20my%20kids%20weren't%20being%20disrespectful.%20They%20weren't%20swearing%20at%20anyone.%20They%20were%20frustrated%2C%20embarrassed%2C%20or%20overwhelmed.%20A%20glass%20would%20break%2C%20a%20homework%20problem%20wouldn't%20make%20sense%2C%20or%20a%20game%20wouldn't%20go%20their%20way.%20The%20word%20they%20used%20was%20simply%20the%20fastest%20way%20to%20express%20how%20they%20were%20feeling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20suddenly%20we%20weren't%20talking%20about%20the%20thing%20that%20upset%20them%20anymore.%20We%20were%20arguing%20about%20the%20word%20they%20chose%20to%20express%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22962bc600-7ded-4fed-a120-d83343f6e80f%5C%22%3EI%20was%20spending%20too%20much%20time%20policing%20language%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20was%20spending%20more%20energy%20policing%20language%20than%20actually%20helping%20my%20kids%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Femotional-intelligence%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enavigate%20their%20emotions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20life%20already%20felt%20full.%20Parenting%2C%20work%2C%20schedules%2C%20responsibilities%20%E2%80%94%20it%20often%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20carrying%20a%20basket%20full%20of%20eggs.%20Every%20small%20rule%2C%20every%20correction%2C%20every%20argument%20was%20another%20egg%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20some%20point%2C%20I%20had%20to%20admit%20that%20the%20basket%20was%20already%20full.%20If%20I%20kept%20adding%20more%2C%20something%20important%20would%20break.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20posing%20for%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69cbf9996a864f6fcd7bbf6a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223213%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20has%20rules%20around%20cursing%20for%20her%20kids.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20started%20letting%20a%20few%20things%20go%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20rule%20about%20curse%20words%20%E2%80%94%20so%20I%20could%20focus%20on%20what%20actually%20mattered%20most%3A%20making%20sure%20my%20kids%20feel%20seen%2C%20heard%2C%20and%20understood%20when%20they're%20struggling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquestions-to-avoid-during-a-job-interview-2016-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erules%20protect%20what%20matters%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Others%20just%20add%20weight%20to%20the%20basket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2230e7bbfa-2c15-47fc-ad3e-43c6ebc8269c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20treat%20cursing%20as%20emotional%20expression%2C%20not%20misbehavior%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20that%20the%20words%20themselves%20weren't%20the%20real%20problem.%20The%20emotion%20behind%20them%20was%20what%20actually%20mattered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKids%20experience%20frustration%20the%20same%20way%20adults%20do.%20The%20difference%20is%20that%20they're%20still%20learning%20how%20to%20manage%20it.%20Sometimes%20that%20learning%20process%20includes%20imperfect%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20treating%20every%20curse%20word%20as%20misbehavior%2C%20I%20started%20thinking%20of%20it%20as%20an%20emotional%20expression.%20If%20my%20child%20mutters%20a%20word%20under%20their%20breath%20after%20dropping%20something%20heavy%20or%20getting%20stuck%20on%20homework%2C%20it's%20usually%20just%20a%20quick%20way%20of%20releasing%20frustration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20shifting%20my%20perspective%2C%20those%20moments%20stopped%20feeling%20like%20something%20that%20needed%20discipline%20and%20started%20feeling%20like%20something%20that%20needed%20understanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cb625d50-27fb-4dc8-8b6a-434bb97abd55%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20set%20flexible%20boundaries%20instead%20of%20banning%20words%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELetting%20go%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bno%20swearing%20ever%26quot%3B%20rule%20didn't%20mean%20anything%20goes.%20We%20still%20have%20clear%20expectations%20about%20when%20and%20where%20certain%20language%20is%20appropriate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20our%20house%2C%20the%20boundaries%20are%20simple%3A%20don't%20swear%20at%20school%2C%20don't%20swear%20at%20people%2C%20don't%20swear%20around%20your%20grandparents%2C%20and%20ideally%20don't%20swear%20around%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20boundaries%20have%20been%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESwearing%20at%20someone%20crosses%20the%20line%20into%20disrespect%2C%20and%20we%20address%20it%20immediately.%20School%20has%20its%20own%20rules%2C%20and%20we%20expect%20our%20kids%20to%20follow%20them.%20And%20around%20grandparents%2C%20we%20simply%20try%20to%20keep%20things%20respectful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20a%20frustrated%20word%20slips%20out%20when%20something%20goes%20wrong%2C%20I%20don't%20turn%20it%20into%20a%20bigger%20issue.%20We%20move%20on.%20In%20our%20home%2C%20the%20focus%20is%20on%20how%20we%20treat%20people%2C%20not%20whether%20every%20sentence%20is%20perfectly%20clean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223056c607-d2cd-4be7-88ce-76a4af3fb440%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDropping%20this%20battle%20removed%20a%20surprising%20amount%20of%20tension%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20surprised%20me%20most%20about%20this%20shift%20is%20how%20quickly%20the%20tension%20around%20language%20disappeared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20every%20small%20slip%20used%20to%20trigger%20a%20correction%2C%20it%20created%20a%20steady%20stream%20of%20tiny%20conflicts.%20Parenting%20already%20involves%20enough%20reminders%20and%20redirections.%20Adding%20language%20policing%20to%20that%20list%20just%20created%20another%20opportunity%20for%20disagreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20stopped%20reacting%20so%20strongly%2C%20those%20moments%20mostly%20faded%20away.%20The%20kids%20weren't%20getting%20much%20of%20a%20reaction%20anymore%2C%20so%20the%20words%20stopped%20feeling%20rebellious%20or%20dramatic.%20They%20simply%20became%20what%20they%20were%20in%20the%20first%20place%3A%20quick%20expressions%20of%20frustration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20house%20felt%20calmer%20almost%20immediately.%20Conversations%20didn't%20escalate%20as%20easily%2C%20and%20small%20moments%20that%20used%20to%20turn%20into%20arguments%20began%20to%20pass%20without%20much%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220863526f-a64e-40b4-9510-71595f13b6f6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20biggest%20benefit%20has%20been%20more%20honest%20communication%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20unexpected%20benefit%20of%20relaxing%20this%20rule%20is%20that%20my%20kids%20talk%20more%20openly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKids%20don't%20always%20have%20the%20vocabulary%20to%20explain%20exactly%20what%20they're%20feeling%2C%20especially%20when%20emotions%20are%20running%20high.%20If%20they%20feel%20like%20every%20sentence%20is%20going%20to%20be%20corrected%2C%20sometimes%20they%20stop%20talking%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20lowering%20the%20pressure%20around%20language%2C%20my%20kids%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20say%20what%20they're%20actually%20feeling.%20Sometimes%20it's%20blunt.%20Sometimes%20it's%20messy.%20But%20it's%20honest.%20And%20honest%20conversations%20are%20much%20easier%20to%20work%20through%20than%20silent%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20getting%20stuck%20correcting%20a%20word%20choice%2C%20we%20can%20focus%20on%20the%20bigger%20conversation%3A%20what%20upset%20them%2C%20what%20went%20wrong%2C%20and%20how%20they%20might%20handle%20it%20next%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22890782fe-2065-4d48-b6e5-e95b2ee0d62b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELetting%20go%20of%20this%20rule%20made%20me%20a%20calmer%20parent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EParenting%20has%20taught%20me%20that%20some%20rules%20deserve%20more%20energy%20than%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESafety%20matters.%20Respect%20matters.%20Responsibility%20matters.%20Those%20are%20the%20things%20we%20focus%20on%20consistently%20in%20our%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELanguage%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20more%20flexible%20than%20I%20once%20believed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20deciding%20that%20curse%20words%20weren't%20the%20hill%20I%20wanted%20to%20die%20on%2C%20I%20removed%20one%20small%20but%20constant%20source%20of%20tension%20from%20our%20home.%20I%20also%20found%20myself%20reacting%20less%20and%20listening%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20the%20end%2C%20that%20shift%20didn't%20just%20change%20how%20my%20kids%20communicate.%20It%20changed%20how%20I%20show%20up%20as%20a%20parent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20house%20isn't%20perfect.%20No%20house%20with%20three%20kids%20ever%20is.%20But%20it's%20calmer%20than%20it%20used%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20sometimes%20that%20kind%20of%20change%20starts%20with%20something%20as%20simple%20as%20deciding%20one%20rule%20just%20isn't%20worth%20the%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-let-my-kids-swear-parenting-lessons-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1775919961000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69cbdd818e5f53c45ea2dd50%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-let-my-kids-swear-parenting-lessons-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22By%20dropping%20the%20no-swearing%20rule%2C%20I%20found%20a%20calmer%2C%20more%20connected%20home%20%E2%80%94%20and%20fewer%20unnecessary%20arguments%20with%20my%20kids.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Hope%20Denton)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-let-my-kids-swear-parenting-lessons-2026-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'We%20have%20to%20get%20ready%20for%20large-scale%20conflicts...we%20need%20a%20different%20military'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1775919720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F26%2F04%2F1920x1080%2Fskynews-general-jennie-carignan_7217210.jpg%3F20260411170433%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwe-have-to-get-ready-for-large-scale-conflicts-says-canadas-military-chief-13530556%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20well%20as%20being%20the%20first%20woman%20to%20lead%20Canada's%20armed%20forces%2C%20General%20Jennie%20Carignan%20is%20also%20in%20command%20as%20her%20country%20pushes%20to%20rearm%20on%20a%20scale%20not%20seen%20since%20the%20Cold%20War.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwe-have-to-get-ready-for-large-scale-conflicts-says-canadas-military-chief-13530556%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nearly%20400%20sentenced%20in%20Nigeria%20for%20links%20to%20mil