steries%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGolf%20Digest%3C%2Fa%3E%20tested%20the%20water%20on%20one%20hole%20in%201996%20and%20reported%20it%20contained%20blue%20food%20dye.%20Augusta%20National%20has%20never%20commented%20publicly%20on%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDyed%20water%20or%20not%2C%20there's%20good%20fishing%20at%20Augusta%20National.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222013%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%2012th%20hole%20at%20the%20Masters.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69d80792f976785dcb18ffd7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221510%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%2012th%20hole%20at%20the%20Masters.%3Cp%3EPatrick%20Smith%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20players%2C%20though%2C%20don't%20like%20to%20talk%20about%20it%20because%20it%20is%20forbidden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202011%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fmonteburke%2F2011%2F04%2F05%2Ffishing-augusta-national%2F%231f44d334684a%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EForbes%3C%2Fa%3E%20interviewed%20golfers%20about%20the%20best%20fishing%20spots%20on%20the%20PGA%20Tour.%20When%20Augusta%20was%20brought%20up%2C%20he%20described%20their%20responses%20as%20%26quot%3Bsqueamish%26quot%3B%20and%20they%20only%20admitted%20to%20hearing%20there%20were%20some%20good%20spots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EFor%20years%2C%20it%20was%20thought%20that%20the%20course's%20lone%20palm%20tree%20was%20a%20myth.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224647%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20people%20walk%20under%20the%20palm%20tree%20at%20Augusta%20National.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69d808c496ef6a4c9d1216c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223485%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMany%20thought%20the%20palm%20tree%20at%20Augusta%20National%20was%20a%20myth.%3Cp%3EAugusta%20National%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20long%20time%2C%20there%20was%20a%20legend%20of%20a%20single%20palm%20tree%20on%20the%20Augusta%20National%20Golf%20Club.%20It%20was%20said%20to%20be%20hidden%20by%20larger%20trees%20on%20the%20fourth%20hole%2C%20and%20only%20golfers%20who%20hit%20a%20terrible%20shot%20into%20the%20woods%20had%20seen%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202006%2C%20the%20fourth%20hole%20was%20lengthened%20to%20ensure%20it%20remained%20challenging%20for%20golfers%20with%20modern%20equipment.%20During%20the%20work%2C%20many%20trees%20were%20removed%2C%20revealing%20the%20lone%20palm%20tree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgolf.com%2Fnews%2Faugusta-national-palm-tree%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGolf.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20there%20used%20to%20be%20more%20palms%20in%20the%20area%20until%20a%20winter%20storm%20destroyed%20all%20but%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EOnly%204%20minutes%20of%20commercials%20per%20hour%20are%20allowed%20during%20the%20broadcast.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222223%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Masters%20TV%20camera%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69d80eda05c9b303c4e76c55%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20CBS%20TV%20camera%20at%20the%20Masters.%3Cp%3ERob%20Brown%2FAugusta%20National%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20seemingly%20unheard%20of%20in%20modern%20sports%20broadcasting%2C%20the%20Masters%20has%20stayed%20consistent%20in%20its%20allotted%20commercial%20time%20over%20the%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.golfmonthly.com%2Fnews%2Fwhy-does-the-masters-coverage-start-late-in-the-day%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGolf%20Monthly%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETV%20commentators%20are%20not%20allowed%20to%20refer%20to%20fans%20as%20%26quot%3Bfans%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bspectators.%26quot%3B%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22911%5C%22%20alt%3