y-newsletter-masters-golf-tournament-merch-gnome-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1775903881000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69d931f896ef6a4c9d121b3e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbi-today-saturday-newsletter-masters-golf-tournament-merch-gnome-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20this%20Saturday%20edition%20of%20Business%20Insider%20Today%2C%20we're%20talking%20about%20gnomes%20and%20other%20goodies%20at%20the%20Masters.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jmckenzie%40businessinsider.com%20(Joi-Marie%20McKenzie)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbi-today-saturday-newsletter-masters-golf-tournament-merch-gnome-2026-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Big%20Short'%20investor%20Michael%20Burry%20lays%20out%20why%20he%20thinks%20high-flying%20tech%20stocks%20are%20even%20pricier%20than%20you%20think%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222335%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Michael%20Burry%2C%20the%20investor%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Big%20Short%26quot%3B%20fame.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69d902dc05c9b303c4e76ecd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221589%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMichael%20Burry%2C%20investor%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Big%20Short%26quot%3B%20fame.%3Cp%3EAstrid%20Stawiarz%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMichael%20Burry%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Big%20Short%26quot%3B%20says%20tech%20stocks%20are%20even%20more%20richly%20valued%20than%20they%20seem.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20investor%20pointed%20the%20finger%20at%20stock-based%20compensation%20in%20a%20lengthy%20Substack%20analysis.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20argued%20that%20Wall%20Street's%20forward%20earnings%20estimates%20for%20the%20Nasdaq%20100%20are%2042%25%20overstated.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI%20boom%20has%20catapulted%20tech%20stocks%20to%20historic%20highs%2C%20with%20many%20trading%20at%20punchy%20valuations.%20They're%20even%20more%20expensive%20than%20they%20appear%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-short-michael-burry-substack-investing-strategy-ai-bubble-stocks-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMichael%20Burry%3C%2Fa%3E%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-short-michael-burry-substack-ai-bubble-stock-picks-bitcoin-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einvestor%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Big%20Short%26quot%3B%20fame%3C%2Fa%3E%20explained%20why%20he%20thinks%20this%20in%20a%20detailed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmichaeljburry.substack.com%2Fp%2Fap-sbc-the-tragic-algebra-recurrence%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESubstack%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20week%2C%20which%20he%20said%20was%20the%20product%20of%20weeks%20spent%20reviewing%20more%20than%201%2C000%20annual%20reports%20from%20Nasdaq%20100%20companies%20going%20back%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurry's%20central%20claim%20is%20that%20companies%2C%20and%20the%20Wall%20Street%20analysts%20who%20cover%20them%2C%20don't%20properly%20account%20for%20the%20full%20costs%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-short-michael-burry-nvidia-stock-earnings-ai-bubble-microchips-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estock-based%20compensation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20they%20should%20include%20the%20money%20spent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarren-buffett-stock-buybacks-reasons-loves-face-bailout-ban-coronavirus-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebuying%20back%20shares%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20offset%20the%20dilution%20they%20cause%2C%20and%20the%20net%20taxes%20related%20to%20the%20shares%20vesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurry%20said%20he%20calculated%20that%20under%20generally%20accepted%20accounting%20principles%20(GAAP)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fnasdaq_100%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENasdaq%20100%3C%2Fa%3E%20earnings%20are%20overstated%20by%20nearly%2020%25%20because%20SBC%20costs%20aren't%20fully%20factored%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20if%20the%20index%20is%20trading%20at%20a%20GAAP%20price-to-earnings%20ratio%20of%2025%2C%20the%20real%20multiple%20is%20closer%20to%2030%2C%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurry%20also%20argued%20that%20Wall%20Street's%20forward%20earnings%20estimates%20are%2042%25%20higher%20than%20actual%20owners'%20earnings%20that%20have%20been%20properly%20adjusted%20for%20SBC%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOf%20every%20dollar%20of%20earnings%20per%20share%20that%20GAAP%20blesses%2C%20shareholders%20see%20only%2083.49%20cents%20of%20that%20dollar%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20wayward%2016.51%20cents%20wave%20crudely%20at%20GAAP%20and%20thumb%20their%20noses%20at%20shareholders%20on%20their%20way%20to%20employees'%20pockets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurry%20wrote%20that%20he%20calculated%20that%20the%2097%20primary%20constituents%20of%20the%20Nasdaq%20100%20reported%20%244.9%20trillion%20in%20cumulative%20GAAP%20net%20income%20over%20the%20decade%20ending%20in%20fiscal%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWall%20Street%20analysts%2C%20in%20part%20by%20adding%20back%20SBC%2C%20pegged%20that%20figure%20at%20%245.8%20trillion.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Burry's%20analysis%20put%20%26quot%3Btrue%20owners'%20earnings%26quot%3B%20at%20%244.1%20trillion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%241.7%20trillion%20gap%20is%20an%20%26quot%3Bearnings%20illusion%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%2C%20as%20it%20reflects%20the%20%26quot%3Bdifference%20between%20what%20shareholders%20really%20owned%20of%20corporate%20earnings%20and%20what%20Wall%20Street%20and%20media%20reported.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWall%20Street%20over%20the%20last%2010%20years%20guided%20investors%20to%2042%25%20more%20earnings%20than%20ever%20actually%20existed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223f9b47f1-72a2-49b2-a4d8-0778f38c70ca%5C%22%3E'Serious%20issue'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBurry%20gave%20Meta%20as%20an%20example%2C%20saying%20it%20had%20overstated%20owners'%20earnings%20by%20about%2020%25%20by%20not%20properly%20accounting%20for%20SBC%20costs%20in%20its%20financials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Meta%20might%20appear%20to%20trade%20at%2019%20times%20forward%20earnings%2C%20its%20real%20forward%20price-to-earnings%20multiple%20is%2024%20once%20SBC%20costs%20are%20factored%20in%2C%20he%20wrote.%20If%20shareholders%20only%20receive%20about%2083%25%20of%20GAAP%20income%2C%20then%20they're%20paying%20a%20multiple%20of%2028%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPutting%20this%20in%20perspective%2C%20if%20Wall%20Street%20earnings%20estimates%20are%20the%20basis%20for%20most%20discussion%20of%20index%20P%2FE%20ratios%2C%20those%20discussions%20are%20entirely%2C%20wholly%2C%20woefully%20misguided%2C%26quot%3B%20Burry%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20criticized%20companies%20for%20treating%20SBC%20as%20%26quot%3Bfree%20compensation%20they%20use%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-memo-nvidia-millionaires-small-workforce-stock-awards-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ekeep%20employees%20happy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20saying%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Bserious%20issue%26quot%3B%20that%20can%20eat%20into%20shareholders'%20long-term%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20investor%2C%20known%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fbig-short-michael-burry-scion-housing-market-bubble-gamestop-stock-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eshorting%20the%20mid-2000s%20housing%20bubble%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20issuing%20cryptic%20warnings%2C%20singled%20out%20Tesla%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.co